<div class="artwork-content">

        <div id="artwork-image">
            <img src="images/172014_2919092.jpg" alt="We Shall Remember!" title="Petr Aleksandrovich Aliakrinskii
(Born Orel, 1892; died Moscow, 1961)
Aleksandr Alekseevich Zharov
(Born Semenovskaia, 1904; died Moscow, 1984), We Shall Remember!"  />          </div>

    <p class="tools">
                          <a href="http://www.artic.edu/aic/collections/exhibitions/TASS/artwork/203970/email"><strong>Email</strong> to a friend</a><br />
                    <a href="http://www.artic.edu/aic/collections/exhibitions/TASS/artwork/203970/print" target="_blank"><strong>Print</strong> this page</a>          </p>
    <!--/tools-->
  
    <div id="artwork-details">
    <div id="tombstone">

    <p>    Petr Aleksandrovich Aliakrinskii<br />
(Born Orel, 1892; died Moscow, 1961)<br />
Aleksandr Alekseevich Zharov<br />
(Born Semenovskaia, 1904; died Moscow, 1984)<br />
    </p>
    <h3><em>We Shall Remember!</em>, TASS No. 0730, May 30, 1943</h3>

    <p>
    Stencil<br />    2060 x 740 mm<br />    The Fascists abandoned the village:<br />
They burned its buildings to the ground.<br />
With their rifle butts they herded<br />
The peaceable villagers into the church.<br />
<br />
They closed the iron gates<br />
And set the church on fire...<br />
They these wild German beasts<br />
Left the area right away...<br />
<br />
Comrade! For this take vengeance<br />
On the brown reptiles.<br />
The enemy cannot escape judgment.<br />
Destroy them, oh soldier, without mercy.<br />    Ne boltai! Collection, Obj: 203970</p>
        
        <!--<p id="dept-gallery">--><!--<br />-->
         <!--</p>-->
    </p>
    </div><!--/tombstone-->

